      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter and bake, 28 to 32 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Grease and line two 20 cm round tins. Whisk together the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{light-brown-sugar}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, {{mixed-spice}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. In a separate bowl, whisk the {{eggs}}, {{vegetable-oil}}, and {{whole-milk}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and stir until just combined. Fold in the {{carrot}} and the {{walnuts}} if using. Divide between the tins and bake for 28 to 32 minutes, until well-risen and a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean. Cool in the tins for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack and cool completely before frosting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the frosting and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the softened {{unsalted-butter}} until smooth. Add the cold {{cream-cheese}} and beat briefly until just combined. Add the sifted {{icing-sugar}} and {{vanilla-extract}} and mix on low speed until smooth. Do not overbeat. The ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "cream cheese frosting",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa6esw6000024v4soh0bt5b"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " should be thick and hold its shape. Spread half over the top of one sponge, place the second sponge on top, and spread the remaining frosting over the top and sides. Refrigerate until ready to serve.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
